The differences between some kinds of Christian beliefs date back to just after Christ’s death. Others date back much further. Here’s what you need to know. Since the establishment of the Catholic Church by Jesus Christ 2, years ago, Christian movements have proliferated and divided into separate denominations. Ultimately, groups are often at odds over differing beliefs in the Bible and how they apply to daily life.

Catholicism is derived from beliefs and practices of the apostles and addresses biblical issues that are not covered in scripture. Often, the issues that caused division would be illegal, whether because they were a threat to political authority as in the case of the Jesuits , or because they went against the established laws of the era.
